General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 interested party. pursuant to G.S. 54-109.18A. The filing of an appeal does not suspend the effect
2 of the an order of the conservation conservation, and this the order remains in force pending final
3 disposition of the appeal by the Commission. At the conclusion of the hearing, the Commission
4 may reverse the order of the Administrator and adopt and approve the credit union's plan to
5 continue operations, affirm the Administrator's order of conservation, or order that other
6 appropriate action be taken."
7 SECTION 7. This act becomes effective January 1, 2026.
